May 29 2006	comfortable at the Comfort Inn	I stayed in a single room. It was small but adequate. The room was clean, bed comfortable and included tea/coffee. The en suite bathroom was also clean with a bath tub that had hot water! As I was on the 4th floor, I appreciated the elevator - not all London hotels have them. Breakfast was continenal but sufficient. Staff at the reception were OK. It is on a quiet street and a short walk from buses, underground and stores. My only problem was that I had two heavy suitcases. It was not pracgtical to take a bus so I wheeled them to the Lancaster Gate tube station. Any one else in this situation would be better advised to use Bayswater tube station - especially coming from Heathrow. Other that that the location was central, safe and fairly quiet. If you want a de luxe accommodation at North American standards this is not for you but for those who want something inexpensive and clean, I would recommend.	
