Apr 3 2005	Small but cheap	We just returned from a week stay at the Comfort Inn Hyde Park. The room was clean, but small. The bathroom was also cramped and had broken tiles. The beds were also uncomfortable. On the good side, the room was clean, and the staff was helpful. And it was cheap. Breakfast each morning consisted of croisants, rolls, juice, ham, cheese, yogurt and cereal. It was fine. If you are looking for a clean, basic inexpensive hotel and do not plan to spend much time in your room, the Comfort Inn Hyde Park is fine. If you are looking for alot of amenities and a large room, stay somewhere else.	
Feb 20 2005	Cheap and worth it	Just returned from a 5 day stay at Comfort Inn Hyde Park. This is a great hotel to stay if you basically need a place to sleep and shower. Arrived on an overnight flight from New York and took the Heathrow express straight to Paddington station. One plus about the Comfort Inn Hyde Park is it's convinient location. It's right on the same street from numerous tube lines tube station and just a 5 minute walk. Plus, there's always people (mainly tourists with their luggages) walking the streets. Hotel desk had my room ready even if I got there an hour early. Since it was a single occupancy must admit the room size was a surprise. It was super small! But then again it was just myself sleeping. The bathroom though was very nice with a somewhat european decor to it. Few negatives: the elevator is slower than a snail. You can spend easily sometimes 5 minutes just waiting for it to hit your floor. Also, while it was peaceful 90 percent of the time the walls are real thin so if you have noisy flatmates beware every slam of their hotel room door will be heard and felt. However, big plus was the breakfast which consisted of fresh bread, cereal, juices, coffee/tea, etc. Excellant way to start the day. All in all, Comfort Inn Hyde Park is a great affordable way to spend one's holiday in London. I wouldn't think twice on booking my next time visiting. Enjoy.	
